Banking Program üè¶

This is a simple command-line Banking Program built with Python. It allows users to check their balance, deposit money, withdraw money, and exit the program.

Features

‚úÖ Show current balance

‚úÖ Deposit money

‚úÖ Withdraw money (with balance check)

‚úÖ Exit the program safely

How to Run

Make sure you have Python 3 installed.

Save the code in a file called banking.py.

Open your terminal and run:

python banking.py

Example Usage
Banking Program
1. Show Balance
2. Deposit
3. Withdraw
4. Exit
Enter your choice (1-4): 1
Your balance is $0.00

Notes

You cannot withdraw more money than your current balance.

Negative amounts are not allowed for deposit or withdrawal.